features: OUR PROMISE TO YOU: Focusing on what's best for your baby and for the earth, we offer disposable alternatives that's free from harmful chemicals, parabens, alcohol, dyes, latex and other preservatives. Our natural baby diaper pants are composed of pure ingredients sourced from responsibly-managed forests.

RASH FREE DIAPER PANTS: Parasol diaper training pants feature RashShield protection. It is perfect for your baby's sensitive skin since the inner lining instantly wicks moisture and locks it down within its super absorbent layers. The diaper pants have an ultra light, super breathable design that provides absolute comfort.

TRAINING DIAPER PANTS: Our diaper pants are great for potty training your kids. They have a high waist design featuring stretchable, non-woven fabric made from chlorine-free wood pulp, that's safe for toddlers. Our natural diaper pack is also available in different sizes making it a great choice for day care centers.

SLEEP WELL, SLEEP TIGHT: Our nighttime diaper pants are tailored to provide easy movement for your little one. This super absorbent active wear for babies has a soft elasticized waist and leg cuffs that prevent overflow and side leaks. The gentle touch of the ultra thin core helps your baby sleep through the night feeling dry and breezy.

NATURAL DIAPERS ON THE GO: Complementing longer sleep stretches, our all natural diaper pants feature soft waistband cushions that rest comfortably against your baby's skin without leaving any marks. Keep your hands mess-free with an effortless diaper pant that's perfect for busy parents who are constantly on the go.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality, accurate sizing
reviews.reviewText: These are great. We needed training pants in a smaller size than typical brands offer since our daughter is potty training but still very long and lanky, and these definitely fit the bill. For reference, she is just over 26 lbs and 35.5" and the size 4 is working very well. They're snug enough not to leak but she definitely has some room to grow too.I was trying to decide between trying these first or trying one of the Korean/Asian brands (milk friends, natural blossom), and honestly the deciding factor was that I could get a smaller pack of these first instead of having to buy a 96 count box and risk them not working for us. These have worked out great, though - they're super soft and we haven't had any leaks or other issues. The tape tab is nice for closing them up when needed. We will stick with what works!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sensitive skin baby & toddler alert!
reviews.reviewText: My 3 y/o struggled with eczema since birth so there were no diapers that was useful. The other great brand I found on amazon has raise its price beyond ridiculousness, but I just found these and they work as great for a slightly lower cost and cuter prints! Definitely recommend although if your baby has a bigger bum, they fit more like a bikini bottom 😂

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars New design has me reconsidering this brand unless they bring back their old design.
reviews.reviewText: I agree with the other recent reviews. These pull up diapers used to be 5 stars and I swore by them. This new design is lacking in so many ways and Is making me regret not stocking up before. They are still super soft which is great but they do rip too easy, and I also find that they aren’t as absorbent and dry as before. I have even had a few leaks at night. Other times i find when I change a night diaper that’s super full my baby feels really damp. He has started getting rashes for the first time since using this brand. Please bring the old design back!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the Amazon availability
reviews.reviewText: Nos encantan!We have been using Parasolco diapers with baby #3. While we loved the perks that come with ordering from their direct website, finding their store here on Amazon was a life saver when life got chaotic. Which every parent knows happens. The company has pretty quick delivery time, (3 days), and through Amazon I think got the diaper training pants in 2 days. The training pants for toddlers are just as great of quality as the infant diapers. The price and value is unmatched, so I highly recommend.
